  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can your remove white underarm stains from shirts?",
  "response": "Removing white underarm stains from shirts can be challenging, but there are several methods you can try. Here are some effective techniques:\n\n1. **Baking Soda and Water Paste:**\n   - Mix baking soda with water to create a thick paste.\n   - Apply the paste directly to the stained area.\n   - Let it sit for at least 30 minutes, or even overnight for tougher stains.\n   - Scrub gently with a soft brush and rinse with warm water.\n   - Launder the shirt as usual.\n\n2. **White Vinegar:**\n   - Soak the stained area in white vinegar for 15-30 minutes.\n   - Rub the fabric together to help lift the stain.\n   - Rinse with warm water and wash the shirt normally.\n\n3. **Hydrogen Peroxide and Baking Soda:**\n   - Mix equal parts hydrogen peroxide and baking soda to form a paste.\n   - Apply the paste to the stain and let it sit for 30 minutes.\n   - Scrub gently with a soft brush, then rinse thoroughly.\n   - Wash the shirt as usual.\n\n4. **Lemon Juice:**\n   - Apply lemon juice directly to the stain.\n   - Let it sit for 15-30 minutes.\n   - Rinse with warm water and launder the shirt.\n\n5. **Dish Soap and Hydrogen Peroxide:**\n   - Mix one part dish soap with two parts hydrogen peroxide.\n   - Apply the mixture to the stained area.\n   - Let it sit for 30 minutes.\n   - Scrub gently with a soft brush and rinse with warm water.\n   - Wash the shirt normally.\n\n6. **Aspirin:**\n   - Crush two aspirin tablets and mix with a small amount of warm water to form a paste.\n   - Apply the paste to the stain and let it sit for 2-3 hours.\n   - Rinse thoroughly and launder the shirt.\n\n7. **Commercial Stain Removers:**\n   - Use a commercial stain remover specially designed for removing deodorant and sweat stains.\n   - Follow the instructions on the product for best results.\n\n**Tips for Prevention:**\n- Allow deodorant to dry completely before putting on your shirt.\n- Use an antiperspirant with fewer additives to reduce residue.\n- Wear an undershirt to create a barrier between your skin and your outer shirt.\n\nAlways test any cleaning solution on a hidden area of the fabric first to ensure it does not damage or discolor the material.",
